                <h1>Understanding Pre-Employment Background Checks</h1>
                <p>A pre-employment background check is a process where employers verify a candidate's credentials and history, including criminal records, education, and work experience. This helps employers ensure they hire trustworthy and qualified individuals. Thorough checks can prevent workplace issues, enhance safety, and maintain company integrity.</p>
